tasks.description:
In `src/main.rs`, the step-comment sequence reads:

```
// ── 2. Start non-blocking audio capture
// ── 3. Elapsed-time counter thread
// ── 4. Block until user presses Enter
// ── 5. Stop capture and encode WAV
// ── 6. Validate python3
// ── 7. Validate ffmpeg
// ── 14. Transcribe          ← should be 8
```

Steps 8-13 were removed during an earlier refactor but the step number was not updated. Renumber `// ── 14. Transcribe` to `// ── 8. Transcribe`.

Note: // ── 15. LLM pipeline was also renumbered to // ── 9. as part of this fix (the PRD only mentioned 14→8 but 15 was equally stale).

`save_hotkey()` and `save_prompt()` in `src/config.rs` are nearly identical — both:
1. Clone `self`, set one field.
2. Serialise with `toml::to_string_pretty`.
3. Write to `.tmp` sibling.
4. Rename with EXDEV fallback.
5. Log warnings on each failure.

The only difference is which field they update. This violates the DRY principle and means any bug fix must be applied twice.

Fix: extract a private `save_config(updated: &AppConfig) -> anyhow::Result<()>` that contains the atomic-write logic. Both `save_hotkey` and `save_prompt` become one-line wrappers:

```rust
pub fn save_hotkey(&self, new_hotkey: &str) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    let mut updated = self.clone();
    updated.hotkey = new_hotkey.to_string();
    save_config(&updated)
}

pub fn save_prompt(&self, stem: &str) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    let mut updated = self.clone();
    updated.selected_prompt = stem.to_string();
    save_config(&updated)
}
```
